_header: As I me lened unto a joyful place
_description: Birds’ matins — ten stanzas rhyme royal

CamTCC601.First Lines:
aS I me lenyd vnto a ioyfull placelusty phebus to superuidehow
                    god almyghty of hys gret gracehad florysshed the erthe on euery
                    side…
CamTCC601.Last Lines:
…The melodyous ympne with gret solaseO lux beata
                        Trinitas
